{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Give tenants the right to terminate short term tenancies if repairs not made",
        "additional_details": "This should apply regardless of whether the landlord has a rent guarantor in place or not to cover the shortfall in rent. Tenants should be able to vacate without a two months\u2019 notice period provided their rent is up to date.",
        "background": "The Government should give all tenants the right to terminate their short term tenancies if the landlord repeatedly ignores reasonable requests for repairs to be made. ",
